    <item>
      <title>The Even More Froggy Outfit</title>
      <author>DietCreamss</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/615542</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/615542#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">16b0baf937abd1bf80477f7f03badf3c8a26bc6d</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 03 Sep 2025 01:33:28 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68b79844c4e4b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68b79854c7afc.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68b7986edb232.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68b7987eb7f1d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Froggy outfit Version 2&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;This update adds full functionality with the dye shop! Head over to Hateno Village to add some extra color to your Froggy Set and add your own personal touch!&lt;br&gt;Additionally- along the lines of customizability, you can now enable both regular and stiletto painted nails to add the cherry on top of your outfit.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In technical areas, I improved the base texture, and I made adjustments to the rig which allows the arms to move much more naturally.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: New dye colors for every dye in the game.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Feature&lt;/em&gt;: New options for regular and stiletto painted nails.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugfix&lt;/em&gt;: Tweaks on the rig to improve movement on both hands but mostly the left one while using Linkle.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Amendment&lt;/em&gt;: Improved texture with less visual discrepancies.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an outfit mod that replaces the froggy set with a cute custom modelled froggy outfit!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- The physics on the frog hat are unfinished currently! -&lt;br&gt; By default the hat has no physics, but you can enable the experimental physics using the mod's options tab within TKMM and checking the enabled box.&lt;br&gt;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br&gt;Install with TKMM, ensure it is above any mods that affect the froggy outfit (character mods, armor mods ect.)&lt;br&gt;This mod was tested on version 1.2.0&lt;br&gt;This mod was designed for and tested on Linkle using the official beta with girly animations, and briefly tested on Link (seems to work fine besides obvious proportion differences, I doubt it would be difficult to add an option for link proportions though so lmk if y'all want it!)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In theory this mod would work for other player models, but if the body is unhidden beneath the armor you will likely experience clipping on the torso, this was the case while testing for the warrior princess (Warrior Princess mod does not appear to use tkmm so I merged the files for testing) &lt;br&gt;If you would like to see compatibility patches made for other player mods let me know and I will see what I can do if enough people want it.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/the_even_more_froggy_set.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/the_even_more_froggy_set_v2.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Armor set</category>
      <category>Models</category>
    </item>
